arts.ttl: Bournemouth to rival West Ham and Eintracht Frankfurt to sign Elye Wahi
arts.sum: The race to sign Marseille centre-forward Elye Wahi (22) is heating up as Bournemouth are set to rival West Ham United and Eintracht Frankfurt, according to L’Equipe. With Egyptian free-scoring…

arts.ttl: GW22 FPL stats: Salah and Isak BLANK in open captaincy battle
arts.sum: More than 5million Fantasy Premier League managers have suffered disappointment so far in Gameweek 22 after captaining Mohamed Salah (£13.7m) or Alexander Isak (£9.4m). This is the second Gameweek in a row, and the fourth time ever, that four active players have been captained by more than a million Fantasy managers, highlighting the range of viable options.

arts.ttl: Newcastle United sent Alexander Isak transfer warning as Erling Haaland contract point made
arts.sum: It makes it difficult for clubs interested in striking a deal for Haaland in the future, with Cole now believing it spells danger for the Magpies and Alexander Isak . Ex-West Ham and Chelsea winger Cole was full for praise for Isak, but warned Newcastle they must win silverware if they want to fend off any potential suitors.
Newcastle United manager Eddie Howe believes "fatigue" played a huge role in his side's 4-1 defeat to Bournemouth at St James' Park in the Premier League.

arts.ttl: Kluivert emerging from dad's shadow as Bournemouth 'dream' of Europe
arts.sum: Justin Kluivert's hat-trick in a superb 4-1 win at Newcastle has Cherries supporters dreaming of European football next season.

arts.ttl: 'Beautiful' - Justin Kluivert smashes Newcastle record at St James' Park and fires Euro warning - Chronicle Live
arts.sum: "Bournemouth did a great job recruiting those kind of players that have a lot of ambition and I think you see that in how we speak about how we want to play in Europe. Bournemouth forward Justin Kluivert has smashed his father's Premier League record for goals scored at St James' Park.

arts.ttl: Ruthless Jacob Murphy hooking explained as Newcastle United star makes brutal demand
arts.sum: Newcastle United dressing room leader Dan Burn warned that no player can make any "excuses" after the 4-1 hiding at home to AFC Bournemouth. Speaking in the immediate aftermath, as the club's nine-game winning streak ended in poor fashion, Burn said on NUFC TV: "It's very disappointing.

arts.ttl: Hat-trick Kluivert as Bournemouth stun Newcastle to go sixth
arts.sum: Justin Kluivert scored a hat-trick as Bournemouth brought Newcastle United’s nine-match winning streak in all competitions to a halt with a 4-1 victory at St James’ Park. Kluivert hammered in a third with a brilliant long-range strike in stoppage time, while Milos Kerkez added a fourth before the end to extend their unbeaten streak to 10 league games.

arts.ttl: Ex-Newcastle star misses match due to car crash as current club issue statement
arts.sum: Former Newcastle defender Paul Dummett reunited with ex-team-mate Mike Williamson at League Two bottom dwellers Carlisle United but was forced to miss Saturday's 1-0 defeat to Bradford City

arts.ttl: Kluivert hammers hat-trick as Bournemouth hit FOUR past Newcastle
